<a name="skipmaincontent"></a><h1 class="bac">Banking Center Channel Market Manager MBA Leadership Development Intern</h1>
<h2 class="bac">Our Business</h2>
<p class="bac">
Global Consumer and Small Business Banking (GCSBB) serves more than 38 million consumer and small business households through a distribution network of 5,800 banking centers, 16,800 ATMs, and the nation’s leading Online Banking and electronic bill pay service.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview</h2>
<p class="bac">
Banking Center Channel Market Manager MBA Internship Program:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Internship program designed to prepare future MBA graduates for specific senior positions within GCSBB.</li>
	<li>The goal is to convert MBA interns into full-time associates upon graduation.</li>
	<li>MBA Internship positions mirror the full-time positions of the Market Manager MBA Leader Development Program</li>
</ul>

<p class="bac">
Key Facts about Global Consumer and Small Business Banking Center Channel Leader Development Program:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Intern assignments are carefully selected according to the developmental needs of each individual participant.</li>
	<li>Each position offers a wide range of responsibilities and business opportunities for the intern.</li>
</ul>
<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Must be a MBA or Master’s candidate at an accredited university or college during the time of the internship (i.e., students who apply for a summer 2008 internship must not have a graduation date prior to August 2008).</li>
	<li>Candidates must be a first year MBA student</li>
	<li>Must possess the authorization to work in the United States</li>
</ul>

<p class="bac">
Minimum of a full-time 10-12 week internship may include the following opportunities:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Business/Market Analysis</li>
	<li>Project management</li>
	<li>Product marketing and development</li>
	<li>Process, design and improvement (Structured Coaching)</li>
	<li>Customer Experience analysis</li>
</ul>

<p class="bac">
Personal characteristics:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Ability to successfully navigate in a complex environment</li>
	<li>Strong leadership potential</li>
	<li>Results oriented, proven high level of performance</li>
	<li>Ability to manage tight deadlines, organize, and prioritize work independently</li>
	<li>Flexibility in exploring a variety of business areas</li>
	<li>Maturity, resourcefulness and integrity</li>
	<li>Geographic mobility</li>
</ul>
<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Interns will have the following reporting structure:</h2>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Report to Division Sales Executive and Division Service Executive</li>
</ul>
<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training</h2>
<p class="bac">
Associates will participate in a formal Education and Orientation program to learn more about Bank of America business, culture and values, as well as to network with Executives and other college hires.  Additionally, interns will participate in various networking and learning opportunities throughout the duration of the summer.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

